reviews.text:
Quality Japanese food with authentic combination of ingredients. 8 course set dinner cost like HK$360.

My man brought me here after a whole week of work, service is great and responsive.
Good for casual dining. Friendly staff. Mildly seasoned and retains the natural tastes for most dishes

Good food and good portion.  Slightly expensive as with most quality Japanese cuisine in HK.  Staff is polite and courteous.  The tuna steak I had wasn't very good, fresh but lots of tendons (420 for a few pcs)
Super nice food, friendly staff, their service is wonderful. Meal set is good for a big guy, and price is really reasonable, recommended for u all!
Very high standard Hokkaido cuisine. Seafood are fresh and wagyu beef is awesome. Highly recommend the Obihiro style pork set, very local taste as in obihiro.
